IN 2011. BUSINESS RETENTION RATES REMAINED STRONG BUT WERE LOWER THAN IN 2011. NEW BUSINESS PREMIUMS IN 2012 DECREASED FROM 2011, LARGELY AS A RESULT OF THE COMPANY'S PRICING STRATEGY, HIGHER

DEDUCTIBLES AND OTHER

PROFITABILITY IMPROVEMENT INITIATIVES. RENEWAL PREMIUM CHANGES REMAINED POSITIVE IN 2012 AND WERE HIGHER THAN IN 2011.

