ON JUNE 7, 2013, THE COMPANY ENTERED INTO A FIVE-YEAR, $1.0 BILLION REVOLVING CREDIT AGREEMENT WITH A

SYNDICATE OF

FINANCIAL INSTITUTIONS, REPLACING ITS THREE-YEAR $1.0 BILLION CREDIT AGREEMENT THAT WAS DUE TO EXPIRE ON JUNE 10, 2013. TERMS OF THE CREDIT AGREEMENT ARE DISCUSSED IN MORE DETAIL IN

NOTE 8 OF NOTES TO THE COMPANY'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

