COMPANY'S $107 MILLION REMAINING AGGREGATE PRINCIPAL AMOUNT OF 6.25% FIXED-TO-FLOATING RATE DEBENTURES BEAR INTEREST AT AN ANNUAL RATE OF 6.25%

FROM THE DATE OF ISSUANCE TO, BUT EXCLUDING, MARCH 15, 2017 AND AT A RATE OF THREE-MONTH LIBOR PLUS 2.215% THEREAFTER. THE TABLE ABOVE INCLUDES INTEREST PAYMENTS THROUGH THE SCHEDULED MATURITY

DATE OF MARCH 15, 2037. INTEREST PAYMENTS BEGINNING MARCH 15, 2017 THROUGH MARCH 15, 2037 WERE CALCULATED USING THE THREE-MONTH LIBOR RATE AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2013.

SEE

NOTE 8 OF NOTES TO THE COMPANY'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS FOR A FURTHER DISCUSSION OF OUTSTANDING INDEBTEDNESS. BECAUSE THE AMOUNTS REPORTED IN THE FOREGOING TABLE INCLUDE

PRINCIPAL AND INTEREST, THE TOTAL LONG-TERM DEBT OBLIGATIONS WILL NOT AGREE WITH THE AMOUNTS REPORTED IN NOTE 8.

